type: Properties derived from RDA elements and relationship designators with the domain of RDA Work.

description (en): Relates a work to a candidate for a degree who defends or opposes a thesis provided by the praeses in an academic disputation.
Relates a work to a character string uniquely associated with a work, or with a surrogate for a work (e.g., an authority record).
note (en): The identifier serves to differentiate that work from other works.

label (en): has other distinguishing characteristic of the work
description (en): Relates a work to a characteristic other than form of work, date of work, or place of origin of the work.
note (en): It serves to differentiate a work from another work with the same title or from the name of a person, family, or corporate body.

description (en): Relates a work to a class or genre to which a work belongs.

Relates a work to a corporate body granting an academic degree.
Relates a work to a corporate body hosting the event, exhibit, conference, etc., which gave rise to a work, but having little or no responsibility for the content of the work.

description (en): Relates a work to a director responsible for the general management and supervision of a filmed performance.

Relates a work to a later work that continues the narrative of an earlier work.

Relates a work to a later work used in place of an earlier work, usually because the later work contains updated or new information that makes the earlier work obsolete.

description (en): Relates a work to a person, family, or corporate body responsible for most of the business aspects of a production for screen, sound recording, television, webcast, etc.

description (en): Relates a work to a person, family, or corporate body responsible for the creation of a work.

Relates a work to a person, family, or corporate body sponsoring some aspect of a work, e.g., funding research, sponsoring an event.

description (en): Relates a work to a person, family, or corporate body to whom a work is dedicated.
Relates a work to a person, family, or corporate body to whom a work or part of a work is addressed.
